\subtree{
\title{Ordered Locale Fanout}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready (Updated Dec 24, 2024) \strong{Trit}: 0 (ERGODIC - coordinator/synthesizer) \strong{Principle}: Cocone over GF(3) ordered locale (Heunen-van der Schaaf) \strong{Platform}: macOS with Apple Silicon + MLX}

\subtree{
\title{Mathematical Foundation (CORRECTED)}
\p{This is now based on \strong{true ordered locales} per Heunen-van der Schaaf (2024):}

\pre{\startverb
An ORDERED LOCALE is:
  1. Frame L (complete Heyting algebra of opens)
  2. Order ≪ on L (between OPENS, not points!)
  3. Open cone condition: ↑U and ↓U are open when U is open
\stopverb}

\p{The fanout is a \strong{cocone} (colimit diagram) over this ordered locale:}

\pre{\startverb
   MINUS(-1)  ERGODIC(0)  PLUS(+1)
       \          |          /
        \    direction      /
         \    0 → 1        /
          \       |       /
           ι₋₁   ι₀    ι₊₁
            \     |     /
             ↘    ↓    ↙
                APEX
              (merged)
\stopverb}

\p{The \strong{ordered locale} structure:}

\ul{
\li{Opens: {MINUS, ERGODIC, PLUS} — no points, just roles}
\li{Order: -1 ≤ 0 ≤ +1 (compatible with meet)}
\li{Direction: flow from validation → coordination → generation}
}

\p{See \code{\startverb ordered-locale\stopverb} skill for formal definition.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{\strong{Ordered Locale Fanout} splits work into 3 parallel agents, each with:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Fixed trit} (-1, 0, +1) determining role}
\li{\strong{Fixed voice/locale} for auditory distinction  }
\li{\strong{Deterministic seed} derived from parent}
\li{\strong{Optional MLX generation} for local LLM inference}
}

\pre{\startverb
                    ┌─────────────────┐
                    │  PARENT AGENT   │
                    │  seed=0x42D     │
                    └────────┬────────┘
                             │ fork(3)
           ┌─────────────────┼─────────────────┐
           ▼                 ▼                 ▼
   ┌───────────────┐ ┌───────────────┐ ┌───────────────┐
   │ MINUS (-1)    │ │ ERGODIC (0)   │ │ PLUS (+1)     │
   │ Anna (German) │ │ Thomas (French)│ │ Luca (Italian)│
   │ VALIDATE      │ │ COORDINATE    │ │ GENERATE      │
   │ seed₀         │ │ seed₁         │ │ seed₂         │
   └───────────────┘ └───────────────┘ └───────────────┘
\stopverb}
}

